JAPAN DAYBOOK: Yen Falls After G-7; Nuclear Crisis Continues

-- B y   E d i t o r :   [ b n : P R S N = 1 7 0 8 2 6 4 8 ]   G e a r o i d   R e i d y   [ ]
-- 
2011-03-18T00:25:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/japan-daybook-yen-falls-after-g-7-nuclear-crisis-continues.html
The yen weakened against the
dollar after Finance Minister  Yoshihiko Noda  said that the G-
7 agreed to join intervention in the  currency markets . The
battle to contain the damage at Tokyo Electric Power Co.’s
damaged Fukushima nuclear power plant continues, with a power
line expected to be connected as early as today.  WHAT TO WATCH
*Tokyo Electric Power may connect a power line to help
 restore the nuclear plant’s cooling systems today.
*The Japanese Cabinet is due to meet today. Finance Minister
 Yoshihiko Noda and Economy Minister Kaoru Yosano will speak
 to reporters after the meeting.
*Chief Cabinet Secretary Yukio Edano updates at 11 am
*Koichiro Watanabe, chairman of the Life Insurance
 Association of Japan, gives a regular press conference at 3
 pm
*Electricity sales for February announced at 11 am
*Steel production figures for February at 2 pm
 